##Why are hospitals in Wuhan still short of supplies?

Wechat, renwumag1980

Feature Introduction, the best Chinese character report

It's not an emergency! Is it gone? "In the past two days, the Wuhan Union Hospital and the central South Hospital have once again raised funds through social media, leading netizens to question: all over the country are donating medical supplies to Wuhan, where are the supplies?

Wen | Yi Fangxing, Zheng Dan
Editor | Goldstone

Wen | Yi Fangxing, Zheng Dan

Editor | Goldstone

Procurement difficulties
Out, out, out

"At first, I thought I'd raise half a million. "

At 10:00 am on January 23,2020, the city of Wuhan was sealed off, and news of a shortage of supplies spread to Wuhan's major hospitals. Among them, two affiliated hospitals of Wuhan University and Zhongnan Hospital called for urgent help from alumni. After 9:00 pm, the Wuhan University bought 1,000 sets of protective clothing by way of advance payment, then she began to recruit, as if she were worth 500,000, as Li Dalin, a 2002 graduate student in Clinical Medicine at Wuhan University, had hoped.

The money came flooding in.

Within an hour of the fundraising message, the goal of $500,000 had been reached, and 39 hours later, the endowment reached the number that alumni members could not have imagined -- a number that would be worth as much as $16 million. During this period, the wechat payment code expired, they had to be replaced with alipay and bank cards.

Donors from all over the country, has long exceeded the scope of alumni Wu. A donor named Ya Jun wrote in the article, "not an alumnus of Wu University, but saw this channel of donation in the circle of friends, and chose to trust, has donated. ". Hope the supplies can be smoothly to Wuhan Medical Staff. "

He was so moved that he joined the alumni purchasing group, responsible for the purchase of medical supplies -- a process that led to the conclusion that fund raising was one of the easiest things to do in non-governmental organization.

The wechat donation page of Wu Da's Fund to fight the new type of pneumonia. Photo: Wuhan University

I spend 16 hours a day looking for supplies. On January 28, Li daling complained about "people" . Including Him, Wu University Alumni Association procurement team of seven people, including the medical group, first-line medical staff, pharmaceutical companies, CDC and other links in the medical chain professionals, but procurement is still difficult.

These days, the most he does is to answer the phone and make phone calls, and the most he hears is "out of stock. ". First, they found a catalogue of medical supplies, listing qualified manufacturers of medical supplies in various parts of the country, calling each day and, within days, calling all the relevant enterprises in the country.

"At present, most of the big factories in the country are connected with the government. What we can really get is only the remaining 10 percent. Once, Li Dalin and his men even paid for the goods, but the goods were requisitioned and the manufacturers refunded the money. On another occasion, he telephoned a factory in a province, which, he said euphemistically, had just donated some medical supplies to Wuhan and now needed to leave some for the local community. He also understood, "the whole of China is fighting the epidemic, and every place should be prepared. ". "

The same is true for the Wu da Shenzhen Alumni Association, which has raised nearly $20 million in a short time, but has struggled to spend it.

In the case of protective clothing, hospitals in Hubei Province currently consume about 100,000 protective clothing per day, according to relevant statistics, but the overall production capacity of protective clothing in China is only 30,000 per day. Liu Yuling of the Shenzhen Alumni Association purchasing group of Wuhan University said that at the beginning, he got the phone numbers of all the protective clothing manufacturers in the country and made a plan to buy as many as he could, but the reality was cruel. He called every morning until 2 a.m, in response to his constant disappointment, "the last thing he needs right now is money. "

Compared with domestic ngos, overseas ngos seem to have less difficulty in purchasing. After all, they hand in many "beautiful" answers. The Huazhong University of Science and Technology in less than a week, we got 25,000 suits, 240,000 medical-grade masks, and 4,000 goggles, but behind it all, there's a story of almost kneeling.

On the 30th day of the Lunar New Year, seeing the epidemic situation in China, the president of the Huakede German Alumni Association, Ye Jiwen, immediately made a decision not to solicit donations, but to find the source of the goods first. He is the founder of the Yiyou Group, a multinational logistics company in its own right with connections in Germany. He learned that the local medical supplies supplier Dach company has a batch of goods, immediately out of his own pocket 200,000 euros all ordered.

But the CEO of Dach suppressed the shipment because, "what if Germany explodes? "? We have to leave masks for German hospitals, too. "Just as the other party was planning a full refund, the vice president of the Alumni Association, Xu Tao, drove to the factory. Xu Tao was engaged in procurement negotiations. He talked with the Germans for over an hour. The other party never relented. He was in a hurry, he showed the video of the Wuhan Hospital, "watching the Germans collapse, " and Xu told the Germans, "if Wuhan can hold out, Germany can hold out! Eventually, the deal was saved by the videos. After the event, Xu Tao said, "doing procurement for so many years, the first time to understand the feeling of shopping almost kneel. ". "

The first batch of goods donated by the Wakkord Alumni Association to the Wuhan Union Hospital has been cleared. Photo Credit: China Red Cross Foundation

Decision making difficult
Protection against premium, protection against scams

These days, when most of the medical supplies that private organizations like the Wuhan University can find are concentrated in the hands of dealers, price is the biggest issue.

One of Li's most outrageous dealers sold N95 masks, which had been on the market for about 6 yuan, for 70 yuan each, a 10-fold increase, while the most Li could accept was less than 20 yuan. He's trying to play the emotional card, but it's not working, "they're all privately run, and they don't care if you're helping a front-line hospital, like he's got 100,000 masks on his hands, he's selling them a little bit more, how much more can he make? Anyway, you don't have to have people. "

"All of our money is donated, and the purchase price must be affordable to the public. After much thought, Li decided to give up the overpriced masks. Later, after consulting with other members, the Beijing Alumni Association of Wuhan University decided that the purchase price of medical supplies should be at most double that of normal times, and that the special ones that are in short supply could be tripled. For example, disposable medical masks used to cost nearly one yuan each. Li Daling saw a supply of 20,000 masks at 2.50 yuan each. "I still thought it was a bit expensive, so I didn't buy them. "

It's so hard to spend money. Li Dalin is inundated with information every day. "when I called, more than 80 percent of the supply information was for civilian use, which the hospital didn't want, and the remaining 10-odd percent was for qualified medical use, but the asking price was too high to buy The remaining less than 5% can be considered, but in the process of checking the enterprise qualifications, or communication negotiations, the goods were robbed. "

In this "panic buying" trend, the selection of procurement information has also become a lot of civil procurement staff face an important problem. For example, a 500-person wechat group called "medical resources mutual help" posts more than 2,000 messages a day, including more than 200 messages from suppliers that need to be screened. In a group like this, there are ten more for every person in charge of purchasing.

One Heart entertainment is a talent agency. According to the old pattern, artists donate money, send a message, and that's it. But this time it was different. What was missing was supplies, so money made sense only if it was made into supplies. So after raising money, the company also began looking for ways to buy medical supplies, hoping to help the hospital from point to point.

At present, the market N95 medical mask has risen to an average price of 16 yuan, and one entertainment purchasing staff Zhang Xue in a pile of information to see an 8.5 yuan offer, so quickly contact each other. A young girl answered the phone and quickly pulled a snow into the crowd. The girl in the group provided a video of a mask, saying that a friend owned the factory and urged everyone to "buy" every day. Eager buyers rushed to sell. Zhang Xue also placed an order for 10,000 masks, worth 85,000 yuan. However, payment, the other side to the order number is a three-nil order, neither the delivery address, also can not find any logistics information.

Zhang Xueji, screenshots, recordings, call to tell the other party to go through legal procedures, finally, the other party promised to "wait two days, if the goods have not arrived on the refund. ".

Buyers are wary of sellers, and sellers are equally wary of buyers.

Zhang Xue met a suspicious factory. This factory in Shandong, specialized in producing medical disposable disinfectant, the other side's question is very sharp: "Who are you? "? What exactly are you buying it for? How are you gonNA prove that you gave it to the hospital? "

In this period, manufacturers will also receive a large number of calls, including some want to buy goods at low prices, and then sell high profit merchants, therefore, manufacturers are also very alert. In addition to issuing each other's business license and other supporting documents, Zhang Xue came up with a way to pull each other to his own hospital docking group, "each other can judge. ". And the place of delivery is written directly on the hospital, we are not involved in the process. "

It took a whole day for her to earn the firm's trust -- An order for 275 boxes of medical hand sanitizer was finally placed.

Li Dalin is also struggling to spend money. According to the latest announcement, as of 6 p.m. on January 29, the Beijing Alumni Association of Wuhan University had bought about 700 N95 masks, 2,500 sets of protective clothing, about 3,600 goggles and 200 medical air sterilizers, and tens of thousands of disposable surgical gowns, surgical gloves, disinfectant and other supplies, the total cost of 5.38 million yuan, less than a third of the total donations. At the same time, the price of goods and materials is getting higher and higher, for example, on January 24, the price of protective clothing was 140 yuan a piece, by January 27, the price of protective clothing has risen to 262 yuan a piece.

In an effort to reassure donors, the Wuhan University displayed the purchased protective material on its official logo. Photo: Wuhan University

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Logistical difficulties
Bad roads, bad deliveries

Zhang felt relieved when she bought 275 cases of disposable medical disinfectant, but soon discovered a bigger problem, these disinfectants can only be delivered in 20 to 60 boxes per day to many hospitals in Hubei -- as if the logistics problem has become the "last kilometre" to restrict the flow of supplies to the front.

At present, large logistics companies such as SF express, debon logistics and Jd.com logistics have joined the Public Welfare transport organized by the government. According to the announcement from JD.com logistics, 20 tons of goods arrive in Wuhan every day. However, these large logistics companies may not be able to pay attention to private donations. Sf Express also issued a notice saying, "in times of emergency, in order to enhance transport efficiency and protect first-line special needs, at present, it is not possible to provide public welfare logistics transportation support for individual donated materials. "

As a result, private institutions to raise the transport of medical supplies more or need to find their own way, but isolated measures to the logistics of transport difficulties.

The first batch of medical supplies purchased by the Beijing Alumni Association of Wuhan University on the 24th were face masks and disposable surgical isolators. "We were very happy to get it, but we couldn't find any truck drivers who wanted to go to Wuhan, because Wuhan is only allowed in and not allowed out. In accordance with the quarantine requirements, foreign vehicles entering Wuhan, drivers should be quarantined for 14 days. "even if it costs $1,000 more, no one will pull it. Unfortunately, the supplier had to ship the goods to Tianmen, and we had to find a way to get them to Wuhan. "

The industry describes the shipment of goods to Wuhan as "No Return" . According to Ai Caijing, an e-commerce company executive revealed that the most difficult and confusing thing now is that the logistics supporting Wuhan are not allowed to leave when they arrive in Wuhan. "The cart is going to run out if this keeps up. "Not only that, but even if they made it to Wuhan and managed to get out, they would still be required to be quarantined for 14 days after returning to their point of departure. "Several head delivery companies have experienced this kind of problem. The number of employees who were on duty during the Spring Festival period was low, but now there are fewer and fewer soldiers. "

The freighter is carrying protective gear. Tu Yuan Ai Economic Agency wechat no

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At the same time, vigilance over Hubei license plate vehicles in other regions has made the entire transportation more and more difficult.

Zhao Jun, a 52 year old native of Xiangyang, Hubei Province, has just returned from a trip to Xiangyang with medical supplies from Changyuanla, Henan Province, comparable to a spy movie. On Jan. 28, he received word from the manufacturer that more than 40,000 masks, 200 protective suits and 200 pairs of goggles he had ordered for donation to the hospital could not be shipped and needed to be picked up by them.

"Changyuan County is the capital of medical supplies in China. Many places use ambulances to look for supplies, and some vice mayors can't even get them. Even so, Zhao Jun says, the situation is critical. In order to hold on to the goods, their suppliers have been staying in the factory, still sleeping in the car at night. If you don't get it, it's gone.

Before he left, he spent a whole day working on the "certificate of transportation of emergency epidemic prevention and support materials" and asked Xiangyang Emergency Command, CDC, Public Security Bureau and hospital to stamp each one, then put the proof in the back of the down jacket like a baby.

A truck driver who was transporting supplies to Wuhan was given a special pass. Image source interface news

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
From Xiangyang to Changyuan County, stopped three times high-speed service area, Zhao Jun wanted to eat bowl noodles, but the other side looked is Hubei license plate, noodles are not allowed to eat, chucked people, "said to hurry not to leave the police. ". "when they got off the highway in Changyuan County, the Zhao Army saw that the area was closed. All foreign cars without proper proof were to be stopped. There was even a car with a local license plate, but the owner of the car was a Guizhou identity card. He quickly produced the certificate, handed it to the police, and kept saying, "we are more than 300 kilometers away from Wuhan, is the only city not closed. ". "

The cops are still hesitating. You can tell they're reluctant. It was "the longest minute of Zhao Jun's life, apart from her daughter-in-law giving birth, " and a cold sweat ran down her back. Finally, I let him through, but I didn't dare to go into the factory. Because the local Hubei license plate is very sensitive, can only about a remote no one place to load the goods, "loading time I feel the factory people than we are also nervous, loaded and ran, the number is not point, not hold hands. ". "

In order to solve the situation of tight logistics capacity in Hubei, the Wuhan Logistics Association organized a "Volunteer Truck Group for Epidemic Prevention" . More than 300 truck drivers who ran in Hubei transportation volunteered to join in, but this is still a drop in the bucket, coupled with the spread of the epidemic, not only is the demand for transport far greater than supply, transport efficiency is also much lower than usual.

Liang Yong, a local truck driver in Wuhan, has been taking part in voluntary transport for five consecutive days. His car is not big, is a red 7 meters 8 van, can load 10 tons, is Wuhan License Plate, in and out of Wuhan without isolation, suddenly become valuable transport, all kinds of logistics work to find him.

On Jan. 28, Liang helped a nongovernmental organization deliver a shipment of goggles and sterile water to the people's Hospital in Foshan, another devastated area around Wuhan. Usually Wuhan to Huanggang, more than an hour may arrive, but now to three hours, because the CDC many checkpoints, each pass, they have to carry out body disinfection, but also to take his temperature.

Previous rainy days in Hubei have also made transportation more difficult. Truck driver Zeng Xiangyu in the transport of goods and materials to take the national road, the car stuck in the mire, did not come out for a day. In addition, many villages and villages in Hubei Road "many are cut off, " transport is even more difficult.

Some truckers don't even have time to change their masks, and they wear one for two or three days. Source: Beijing News

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hospitals are hard
Civilian materials can be used for emergency relief, but they are in short supply

Direct fundraising via social networks has never been attempted before in most public hospitals. A doctor at a third-tier Hospital in Wuhan, who did not want to be named, said it was common practice for departments to ask purchasing departments for their needs, and then seek applications from headquarters. But it's too late now. private-to-private donations are much faster than this process. "

Usually, the hospital will directly announce the doctor's phone number of the materials collected on the collection announcement. After private organizations see this, they will pull the doctors of different hospitals into their respective donation groups and carry out the distribution of materials. After the hospital receives the donations, the doctors will take pictures and send them to the docking bay to confirm.

Wu Yang, Deputy Secretary-general of Wu University's Internet Ai Division, calls this "decentralization. ". This model will greatly improve the communication efficiency of donations, but the donation efficiency is not high at the beginning.

Wangliang (constellation) is a doctor in charge of receiving materials at a hospital in Wuhan. In order to find materials, he added seven or eight groups of docking hospitals. Every day, he connects various kinds of information in the group, his hospital has also received many medical supplies from private institutions, but only 20% of the supplies meet clinical medical standards.

"On the 27th, I got a phone call that a courier had sent me down. I was very excited. I called two colleagues to go down and carry it. The result was a batch of black face masks that did not specify the standard. Four boxes of these we did not dare to use. On the morning of the 28th, I received them again, it was an N95 mask, two cases, but it came with a suction valve, which we passed on to the doctors in the back. At this time our own department only 40 N95 masks, very urgent, and then I received a courier in the afternoon, opened a look is hand sanitizer, this we can use, but not the most urgent shortage. "

Medical supplies are special commodities, said Liu Yuling, a purchasing officer with the Shenzhen Alumni Association of Wuhan University. Medical Masks in China are classified into three categories: medical protective masks (N95) , medical surgical masks and disposable masks. Different standards are applied among the various types, with wide price differences and different ranges of use. Among them, the first-line medical staff needs medical protective masks in accordance with GB19083-2010, such as University of Martial Arts, huake Alumni Association, because the procurement staff are engaged in the medical profession alumni, so it is more strict than ordinary private institutions, the procurement of medical supplies also has a higher qualification rate.

To address the quality of donations, Wangliang (constellation) would then ask private organizations to take photos of their purchases. "If they find a source of supply, they will immediately post a photo in the group and ask us if it works, and if we see it works, " he said, they will arrange for direct delivery to the hospital, but logistics is what they do, and frankly very grateful to them. "

"people" contacted more than 20 front-line hospital materials procurement personnel, the other side said that civilian donations of materials to help them a lot.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the case of adequate protective materials, each medical staff needs to use three protective clothing per day to effectively protect themselves. Image source video screenshot

"I think the biggest help we have from the people is that in the days before the official application came down, the medical supplies from the people have been in great need. "We haven't received anything from the Red Cross since the outbreak, " the head of the Procurement Department at another Wuhan Hospital told people. "By contrast, there has been a steady flow of private donations. On January 27, he said, his hospital had just over 300 N95 masks left, barely enough for one day, but "we were delighted to receive a batch of 500 AMERICAN-STANDARD N95 masks donated from the United States, another day and a half. "

It is also the most effective form of non-governmental donation, as a kind of emergency treatment, but the occasional emergency treatment can not solve the problem of medical shortage in Wuhan and surrounding hospitals, since January 23, when the city was shut down and the epidemic intensified, donations from non-governmental organizations have been very encouraging. However, the difficulties in procurement and logistics have made the materials raised a drop in the bucket compared with the huge gap in the hospitals.

Doctors at a third-tier hospital in Wuhan said that patients in their hospital had installed two buildings, with thousands of medical staff in both buildings, and that each day consumed 1,000 N95 masks, 1,000 protective clothing and 1,000 pairs of goggles. And this is in the medical staff every day to do with the premise of statistics.

This is just one hospital, according to Wuhan's "7 + 7" model, a total of 14 hospitals into the front line of the fight against the epidemic, the daily light designated hospitals consume tens of thousands of protective masks, protective clothing, goggles.

On January 30 and 31, Wuhan Union Hospital and Zhongnan Hospital again used social media to solicit information. Both hospitals used lots of exclamation marks in their announcements, and both said urgently: "NOT URGENT! "! No, there isn't! " He even said, "as long as you get up to standard medical supplies, the postage can be paid ! "

To this, Wu University Beijing Alumni Association buyer Li Dalin is quite helpless, "We try our best to find materials, the result is now the opposite hospital medical supplies or lack. ". "

However, there is also good news. The first batch of clinical medical supplies donated jointly by the Huazhong University of Science and Technology and the Beijing Alumni Association, together with the medical supplies entrusted by the German Tongji Alumni Association to the Huakede Alumni Association, have arrived in Wuhan, more than 400,000 masks, 25,000 protective clothing and 4,000 masks are being distributed to hospitals in and around Wuhan in the order of registration, a similar amount of follow up supplies began boarding planes for Wuhan on China Standard Time.

However, this success is not easy to replicate, because, "Germany has confirmed patients, we have scheduled follow-up materials, German enterprises have been retained for Germany. ". "said Khuako, president of the German Alumni Association.

(at the request of the interviewee, Zhao Jun, Zhang Xue and Wangliang (constellation) are all pseudonyms)
